reut2-000.sgm, REPUBLICANS EYE BIGGER U.S. CONSERVATION RESERVE, A group of Republican governors andmembers of Congress said they intended to explore expanding theconservation reserve program by up to 20 mln acres.    Under current law, between 40 and 45 mln acres of erodibleland must be enrolled in the program by the end of fiscal 1990.    The Republican Task Force on Farm and Rural America, headedby Senate Majority Leader Robert Dole (Kan.), said they wouldconsider drafting legislation to increase the reserve bybetween 15 and 20 mln acres.    Sen. Charles Grassley (R-Iowa) told Reuters he would offera bill to expand the reserve to 67 mln acres. Reuter&#3;
