reut2-000.sgm, U.S. M-1 MONEY SUPPLY ROSE 2.1 BILLION DLRS, U.S. M-1 money supply rose 2.1 billiondlrs to a seasonally adjusted 736.7 billion dlrs in theFebruary 16 week, the Federal Reserve said.    The previous week's M-1 level was revised to 734.6 billiondlrs from 734.2 billion dlrs, while the four-week movingaverage of M-1 rose to 735.0 billion dlrs from 733.5 billion.    Economists polled by Reuters said that M-1 should beanywhere from down four billion dlrs to up 2.3 billion dlrs.The average forecast called for a 300 mln dlr M-1 rise. Reuter&#3;
reut2-000.sgm, GENERAL BINDING &lt;GBND> IN MARKETING AGREEMENT, General Binding Corp said it reacheda marketing agreement with Varitronic Systems Inc, amanufacturer and marketer of electronic lettering systems.    Under terms of the agreement, General Binding will carryVaritronics' Merlin Express Presentation Lettering System, aportable, battery-operated lettering system which produces typeon adhesive-backed tape. Reuter&#3;
