reut2-000.sgm, PAINEWEBBER&lt;PWJ> UNIT UPS SHAER SHOE &lt;SHS> STAKE, Mitchell Hutchins Asset ManagementInc, a New York investment firm and subsidiary of PaineWebberGroup Inc, said it raised its voting stake in Shaer Shoe Corpto 76,000 shares, or 7.5 pct, from 52,100 shares, or 5.1 pct.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,Mitchell Hutchins said it bought 11,900 shares between Jan 8and Feb 24 at prices ranging from 12.125 to 12.75 dlrs a shareand obtained voting control over another 12,000 shares.    The firm has said it bought the stake as an investment onbehalf of its clients, but said it has had discussions withShaer management. It did not disclose the topic of the talks. Reuter&#3;
